How to Install Express + TypeScript

Dependencies
    Nodejs


Install Steps
    1. Inside the Folder Backend run inside the terminal
        npm init --yes
        npm install express

    2. Inside the Folder Backend run inside the terminal
        npm i -D typescript @types/express @types/node
        npx tsc --init

    3. Inside the file ./BackEnd/tsconfig.json uncomment the key:value "outDir" and specify the output path
        "outDir": "./dist",             /* Specify an output folder for all emitted files. */

    4. Modules/Libries -> nodemon don't need to restart the server to apply modifications | concurrently alternative for "&" unix command (multiplataform)  
        npm install -D concurrently nodemon

    5. Substitute the code below inside ./BackEnd/package.json
        "scripts": {
            "build": "npx tsc",
            "start": "node dist/index.js",
            "dev": "concurrently \"npx tsc --watch\" \"nodemon -q dist/index.js\""
        }

    6. Create a example server copy the code below inside ./BackEnd/index.ts
        
        import express, { Express, Request, Response } from 'express';

        const app: Express = express();
        const port = 8080;

        app.get('/', (req: Request, res: Response) => {
            res.send('Express + TypeScript Server');
        });

        app.listen(port, () => {
            console.log(`⚡️[server]: Server is running at http://localhost:${port}`);
        });



    7. Init the Server
        npm run dev